<% content_for :header_includes do %>
  <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/bx_styles/bx_styles.css" />
  <script src="/jquery.bxSlider.min.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
  
  <script type="text/javascript">
  $(document).ready(function(){
    $('#testimonial_slider').bxSlider();
  });
</script>
<% end %>

<div class="introduction">
  <h2>myNHS</h2>
  <p>
    myNHS allows you to manage all interaction with the NHS, including booking
    appointments with your General Practitioner and seeing medical health
    services near you. 
  </p>
  <p>
    Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum.
  </p>
  <%= link_to "View local medical services", patient_maps_path, :class => "button blue bigrounded" %>
</div>
<div class="testimonial">
  <h3>Testimonials</h3>
  <ul id="testimonial_slider">
    <li>
      <p>
        <%= image_tag 'person1.jpg', :width => 280 %>
        MyNHS is amazing for use on the go when using the Windows Phone 7 app. It is extremely easy
        to use and this, along with its incredibly simple interface, allows me to order my prescription.
        I can then go and collect the prescription using the QR image automatically send to my phone.
      </p>
      <div class="credit">Clive Jones, Brighton</div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        MyNHS is extremely simple to use, but still remains very powerful. It is the ease of
        prescribing treatment for my patients that amazes me - there wasn't even any
        upgrading of my computer system as it is all web-based.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        On MyNHS I can very easily find my local health services. I can simply type my
        postcode, then see the contact details and quality information for my local hospitals.
        I can also book appointments with my GP online, as well as seeing the history of my
        health and prescriptions.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>
</div>
<div class="buttons_container"> 
<% css_class = "button blue bigrounded" %>
<%= link_to "Medical Map", patient_maps_path, :class => css_class  %>
<%= link_to "Book an Appointment", patient_gp_bookings_path(params[:patient_id], @patient.gp_id), :class => css_class  %>
<%= link_to "My Prescriptions", patient_prescriptions_path(params[:patient_id]), :class => css_class  %>
<%= link_to "My History", url_for(:controller => "static", :action => "patient_history"), :class => css_class  %>
</div>